	<text><![CDATA[I have consistently preached that nonviolence demands that the means we use must be as pure as the ends we seek. I have tried to make clear that it is wrong to use immoral means to attain moral ends. But now I must affirm that it is just as wrong, or perhaps even more so, to use moral means to preserve immoral ends.]]></text>
 	<author><![CDATA[Martin Luther King Jr.]]></author>
  	<reference><![CDATA[Letter from a Birmingham Jail (1963)]]></reference>
